**5.2 The Risk: AI-Derived Data vs Lab-Confirmed Data**

> ARCHITECTURE RISK --- AI PROVENANCE GAP:\
> \
> The cfi_solutions table stores \'data lake from AI research runs\' but
> has NO confirmed schema.\
> If cfi_solutions rows have no is_ai_generated flag, they cannot be
> programmatically filtered\
> from lab-confirmed canonical values in cfi_feedstock_values.\
> \
> In the fertiliser business, a regulator or EIB auditor asking \'where
> did this NPK value\
> come from?\' must receive: Author + Year + Journal (Lab-Confirmed) OR
> Claude session ID\
> + persona + confidence level (AI-Derived). The current DB provides
> neither systematically.\
> \
> SPECIFIC EXAMPLES OF UNTAGGED AI DATA IN CURRENT DB:\
> - cfi_soil_profiles: all rows tagged LDE (Literature-Derived
> Estimates) --- GOOD\
> - cfi_feedstock_values: no confidence_level or source field ---
> UNKNOWN provenance\
> - cfi_biological_library: 43 organisms --- source of each organism
> property unknown\
> - cfi_solutions: schema unknown --- may have zero provenance fields

**5.3 Recommended AI Provenance Patch (SQL)**

QA INSTRUCTION: Generate the following SQL migration as Migration 10 and
present to Sharon for review:

\-- CFI MIGRATION 10 --- AI Provenance Fields

\-- Adds AI tracking columns to all core tables lacking them

\-- Run in fresh Supabase SQL Editor tab

ALTER TABLE cfi_feedstock_values

ADD COLUMN IF NOT EXISTS confidence_level TEXT

CHECK (confidence_level IN
(\'LDE-HIGH\',\'LDE-MODERATE\',\'LDE-LOW\',\'LAB-CONFIRMED\')),

ADD COLUMN IF NOT EXISTS data_source TEXT,

ADD COLUMN IF NOT EXISTS is_ai_generated BOOLEAN DEFAULT FALSE,

ADD COLUMN IF NOT EXISTS is_approved BOOLEAN DEFAULT TRUE,

ADD COLUMN IF NOT EXISTS created_by TEXT DEFAULT \'canonical_lock\';

ALTER TABLE cfi_chemical_library

ADD COLUMN IF NOT EXISTS warning_level TEXT CHECK (warning_level IN
(\'AMBER\',\'RED\',\'GREEN\',\'NONE\')),

ADD COLUMN IF NOT EXISTS warning_reason TEXT;

ALTER TABLE cfi_biological_library

ADD COLUMN IF NOT EXISTS warning_level TEXT CHECK (warning_level IN
(\'AMBER\',\'RED\',\'GREEN\',\'NONE\')),

ADD COLUMN IF NOT EXISTS warning_reason TEXT,

ADD COLUMN IF NOT EXISTS titre_decay_threshold TEXT;

\-- Set NaOH warning

UPDATE cfi_chemical_library SET warning_level = \'AMBER\',

warning_reason = \'Sodium accumulation risk --- monitor soil Na levels\'

WHERE chemical_name ILIKE \'%NaOH%\' OR chemical_name ILIKE \'%sodium
hydroxide%\';

\-- Set Bt/Provibio ICBB 6095 warning

UPDATE cfi_biological_library SET warning_level = \'AMBER\',

titre_decay_threshold = \'10\^4 CFU/g --- confirm before S4 BSF
loading\',

warning_reason = \'Apply S3 composting phase only. Confirm titre decay
before S4.\'

WHERE organism_name ILIKE \'%thuringiensis%\' OR strain_id = \'ICBB
6095\';

**5.4 cfi_solutions Table --- Schema QA**

QA INSTRUCTION: Run the following query in Supabase to inspect the
actual schema of cfi_solutions:

SELECT column_name, data_type, is_nullable, column_default

FROM information_schema.columns

WHERE table_name = \'cfi_solutions\'

ORDER BY ordinal_position;

Expected minimum fields for AI research outputs:

-   research_question TEXT --- the prompt/question submitted

-   source_model TEXT --- AI model used (claude-sonnet-4-6, perplexity,
    etc.)

-   persona_used TEXT --- expert persona(s) active during run

-   confidence_level TEXT --- LDE-HIGH / LDE-MODERATE / LDE-LOW

-   source_citations JSONB --- array of Author/Year/Journal/DOI

-   is_approved BOOLEAN --- Sharon review gate

-   run_date TIMESTAMPTZ --- when the research run occurred

-   applied_to_table TEXT --- which Supabase table was updated from this
    run

